Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In the above global summary, there is still identified transmission ongoing in Pakistan as seen by the positive environmental sample in Karachi as well as the early report on a case of WPV1 associated disease in Karachi. It will be interesting to learn of the genetic profile of the environmental isolates in Karachi (from this past week as well as from a few weeks ago) and compare them with the newly identified WPV1 associated case in Karachi to see if they are genetically related.

There has been more activity associated with cVDPV2 in both Syria and the Democratic Republic of the Congo (Congo DR), with 6 newly confirmed cases in Syria and 1 newly confirmed case in the DR Congo. According to the Situation Report in section [2] above, there are still 5 additional PV2 (poliovirus type 2) isolates in Syria undergoing final testing -- 4 from Deir al Zour and 1 from Raqqa. Hence there will probably be more cases confirmed in the coming days or weeks. I have not been able to identify similar report information from the DR Congo outbreak so it is not clear if the transmission has been interrupted leaving a total of 8 cases, or if there are still probable cases pending confirmation.

A map showing the global distribution of all WPV1 associated cases and cVDPV associated cases can be found at: http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/.

HealthMap/ProMED maps can be found at:
Syria: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5287768,86
Pakistan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5287768,140
DR Congo: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5287768,194
- Mod.MPP]
